    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<a href="http://sarit.indology.info/"><span style="font-size:
      small;">SARIT: Search and Retrieval of Indic Texts</span></a><br
      /><blockquote class="tr_bq"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><img
      alt="http://sarit.indology.info/images/indolib_logo.png" class="decoded"
      src="http://sarit.indology.info/images/indolib_logo.png" />
      </span></blockquote><blockquote class="tr_bq"><span style="font-size:
      x-small;"><b>SARIT </b>has two interfaces: <b> <a
      href="http://sarit.indology.info/" title="SARIT: Basic Search Interface">Basic
      Search</a> </b>and <b> <a href="http://sarit.indology.info/advanced.shtml"
      title="SARIT: Advanced Search Interface">Advanced Search</a> </b>. Assistance is
      available through the <a href="http://sarit.indology.info/searchterms.shtml" title="SARIT:
      Search Term Help">Search Term Help</a>. <br /> <br /> </span><br
      /><span style="font-size: x-small;"> </span><br /><div
      style="background-color: #f1f1f1; border: 1px solid rgb(68, 68, 68); color: black; margin: 0px
      15px 30px; padding: 15px 30px 25px 35px;"><span style="font-size:
      x-small;"><b>SARIT</b>displays Indological texts marked up according to <a
      href="http://www.tei-c.org/" title="External Link - The Text Encoding Initiative: Yesterday's
      information tomorrow">Text Encoding Initiative (TEI)</a>guidelines. It uses a modified
      version of <a href="http://sites.google.com/site/philologic3/" title="External Link -
      PhiloLogic™">PhiloLogic™</a>, a platform developed by the <a
      href="http://humanities.uchicago.edu./orgs/ARTFL/" title="External Link - ARTFL
      Project">ARTFL Project</a>and <a href="http://dldc.lib.uchicago.edu/"
      title="External Link - Digital Library Development Center">Digital Library Development
      Center</a>at the <a href="http://www.uchicago.edu/" title="External Link - University
      of Chicago">University of Chicago</a>. PhiloLogic™ is widely deployed in the digital
      humanities as a full-text search, retrieval and analysis tool for large TEI document
      collections. Notable installations include <a
      href="http://www.lib.uchicago.edu/efts/PERSEUS/" title="External Link - Perseus Project Texts
      Loaded under PhiloLogic™">Perseus Project Texts Loaded under PhiloLogic™</a>and the
      <a href="http://dsal.uchicago.edu/dictionaries/" title="External Link - Digital Dictionaries
      of South Asia">Digital Dictionaries of South
      Asia</a>.</span></div><span style="font-size: x-small;">
      <b>SARIT</b>provides Indologists with machine readable texts and digital
      instruments for philological research. Currently text search, retrieval and analysis is
      available for <a
      href="http://sarit.indology.info/newphilo/search3t?dbname=indologica&amp;word=&amp;OUTPUT=conc&amp;CONJUNCT=PHRASE&amp;DISTANCE=3&amp;title=&amp;author="
      title="SARIT: Currently available works">these works</a>. All texts accessible through
      the <b>SARIT</b>web interface are available for <a
      href="http://sarit.indology.info/downloads.shtml" title="SARIT: Text Archive Downloads">
      <b>download</b> </a>. </span><span style="font-size:
      x-small;"><br /></span><span style="font-size: x-small;"><br
